H.B. 376
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Mar 11, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH30151-BR-1
Short Title: Various On-Site Wastewater & Well Provisions. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Brody.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MAKE VARIOUS CHANGES TO ON-SITE WASTEWATER PROVISIONS,
3 TO ESTABLISH THE PRIVATE DRINKING WATER WELL TASK FORCE, AND TO
4 ALLOW CERTAIN CERTIFIED WELL CONTRACTORS TO PERFORM WELL SITE
5 EVALUATIONS.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7
8 ON-SITE WASTEWATER BOARD CHANGES
9 SECTION 1.(a) G.S. 90A-73 reads as rewritten:
10 "§ 90A-73. Creation and membership of the Board.
11 (a) Creation and Appointments. – There is created the North Carolina On-Site
12 Wastewater Contractors and Inspectors Certification Board. The Board shall consist of nine
13 members appointed to three-year terms as follows:
14 …
15 (j) Term Limits. – No member of the Board may serve more than two consecutive
16 three-year terms."
17 SECTION 1.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to Board
18 terms beginning on or after July 1, 2026.
19 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 90A-77, as amended by S.L. 2024-49, reads as rewritten:
20 "§ 90A-77. Certification requirements.
21 (a) Certification. – The Board shall issue a certificate to an applicant who satisfies all of
22 the following conditions:
23 (1) Is at least 18 years of age.
24 (2) Submits a properly completed application with all required supporting
25 documents for the certification being applied for to the Board.
26 (3) For grade level II contractor certification, applicant shall satisfy the following
27 conditions:
28 a. Complete the basic on-site wastewater education approved by the
29 Board for any level.
30 b. Complete any additional class hours required for grade level II.
31 (3a) For grade level IV contractor certification, applicant shall satisfy the following
32 conditions:
33 a. Hold current and satisfactory certification of grade level II for a
34 minimum of two years prior to application for grade level IV.
35 b. Complete any additional class hours required for grade level IV.
36 (3b) For inspector certification, applicant shall satisfy the following conditions:
*DRH30151-BR-1*

