27 …."
28 SECTION 3.(b) G.S. 130A-336 reads as rewritten:
29 "§ 130A-336. Improvement permit and construction authorization required.
30 (a) Any proposed site for a residence, place of business, or place of public assembly in
31 an area not served by an approved wastewater system shall be evaluated by either (i) the local
32 health department in accordance with rules adopted pursuant to this Article or (ii) by a
33 professional engineer, licensed soil scientist, or licensed geologist acting within the engineer's,
34 soil scientist's, or geologist's scope of work, as applicable, and pursuant to the conditions of the
35 engineered option permit in G.S. 130A-336.1 or the Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator
36 permit option in G.S. 130A-336.2. An improvement permit issued by a local health department
37 shall include:
38 (1) For permits that are valid without expiration, a plat, or, for permits that are
39 valid for five years, A plat or a site plan.
40 (2) A description of the facility the proposed site is to serve.
41 (3) The proposed wastewater system and its location.
42 (4) The design wastewater flow and characteristics.
43 (5) The conditions for any site modifications.
44 (6) Any other information required by the rules of the Commission.
45 Neither the improvement permit nor the construction authorization shall be affected by change
46 of ownership of the site for the wastewater system provided both the site for the wastewater
47 system and the facility the system serves are unchanged and remain under the ownership or
48 control of the person owning the facility. No person shall commence or assist in the construction,
49 location, or relocation of a residence, place of business, or place of public assembly in an area
50 not served by an approved wastewater system unless an improvement permit and a construction
51 authorization are obtained from the local health department unless that person is acting in
