13 person is acting in accordance with the conditions and criteria of an engineered option permit
14 pursuant to G.S. 130A-336.1 or the Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator permit option
15 pursuant to G.S. 130A-336.2. No improvement permit or construction authorization shall be
16 required for maintenance of a wastewater system. The Department and the local health
17 department may impose conditions on the issuance of an improvement permit and a construction
18 authorization. The Department or the local health department may delay the start of construction
19 of any system until a verification shows that site conditions are unchanged from the issuance of
20 the improvement permit, except that the verification shall not include a geological soil
21 assessment. The owner of the proposed wastewater system may accept or decline the findings of
22 a reassessment of the soils on the site.
23 …."
24 SECTION 3.(c) G.S. 130A-337 reads as rewritten:
25 "§ 130A-337. Inspection; operation permit required.
26 (a) No system of wastewater collection, treatment and disposal shall be covered or placed
27 into use by any person until an inspection by the local health department has determined that the
28 system has been installed or repaired in accordance with any conditions of the Improvement
29 Permit, the rules, and this Article.
30 (a1) Notwithstanding subsection (a) of this section, an applicant may contract with an
31 Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator certified pursuant to Article 5 of Chapter 90A of the
32 General Statutes or an engineer licensed pursuant to Chapter 89C of the General Statutes to
33 conduct any required verifications or inspections. The evaluator or engineer shall provide the
34 applicant with written verification that all conditions of the Improvement Permit and
35 Construction Authorization have been met, including an as-built drawing meeting the standards
36 and scale of the local health department issuing the Construction Authorization as certified by
37 the evaluator. evaluator or engineer. The applicant may cover the system and place it into
38 operation upon receipt of the evaluator's written verification and shall submit the verification to
39 the local health department within two business days of receipt of the verification. The
40 Department, the Department's authorized agents, and the local health department shall be
41 discharged and released from any liabilities, duties, and responsibilities imposed by statute or
42 common law from any claim arising out of or attributed to the on-site wastewater system
43 installation.
44 …
45 (b) Upon determining that the system is properly installed or repaired and that the system
46 is capable of being operated in installation or repair of a wastewater system in accordance with
47 the conditions of the Improvement Permit, the rules, this Article and any conditions to be imposed
48 in the operation permit, Permit and the Construction Authorization, including any site
49 modification conditions noted in the Improvement Permit or Construction Authorization, as
50 applicable, applicable, or upon receipt of written verification submitted pursuant to subsection
51 (a1) or (a2) of this section, the local health department shall issue an operation permit authorizing
